Description.Value: An View object represents a simple 2D view of the map.This is the object to act upon to change the center, resolution, and rotation of the map.
Description.Name: Description

Center.Name: Center
Center.Description: The initial center for the view. The coordinate system for the center is specified with the projection option. Default is undefined, and layer sources will not be fetched if this is not set.

TopLeft.Name: Top Left
TopLeft.Description: Coordinate of the top left of the view, required to calculate local centers on the nodes

BottomRight.Name: Bottom Right
BottomRight.Description: Coordinate of the bottom right of the view, required to calculate local centers on the nodes

EnableRotation.Name: Enable Rotation
EnableRotation.Description: Enable rotation. Default is true. If false a rotation constraint that always sets the rotation to zero is used. The constrainRotation option has no effect if enableRotation is false.

Extent.Name: Extent
Extent.Description: The bounding extent for layer rendering. The layer will not be rendered outside of this extent: [MinX, MinY, MaxX, MaxY]

Projection.Name: Projection
Projection.Description: The projection. Default is EPSG:3857 (Spherical Mercator).

Resolution.Name: Resolution
Resolution.Description: The initial resolution for the view. The units are projection units per pixel (e.g. meters per pixel). An alternative to setting this is to set zoom.

Rotation.Name: Rotation
Rotation.Description: The initial rotation for the view in radians (positive rotation clockwise).

Description.Value: Feature format for reading and writing data in the GeoJSON format.
Description.Name: Description

GeometryName.Name: Geometry Name
GeometryName.Description: Geometry name to use when creating features.

Description.Value: Set fill style for vector features.
Description.Name: Description

Description.Value: Set stroke style for vector features. Note that the defaults given are the Canvas defaults, which will be used if option is not defined.
Description.Name: Description

Description.Value: Container for vector feature rendering styles. Any changes made to the style or its children through set*() methods will not take effect until the feature or layer that uses the style is re-rendered.
Description.Name: Description

Description.Value: Layer source for Bing Maps tile data.
Description.Name: Description

MaxZoom.Name: Max Zoom
MaxZoom.Description: Max zoom. Default is what's advertized by the BingMaps service.

CrossOrigin.Name: Cross Origin
CrossOrigin.Description: The crossOrigin attribute for loaded images. Note that you must provide a crossOrigin value if you are using the WebGL renderer or if you want to access pixel data with the Canvas renderer

Extent.Name: Extent
Extent.Description: Extent for the tile grid. No tiles outside this extent will be requested

Origin.Name: Origin
Origin.Description: The tile grid origin, i.e. where the x and y axes meet ([z, 0, 0]). Tile coordinates increase left to right and upwards

Resolutions.Name: Resolutions
Resolutions.Description: Resolutions. The array index of each resolution needs to match the zoom level. This means that even if a minZoom is configured, the resolutions array will have a length of maxZoom + 1

TileLoadFunction.Name: Tile Load Function
TileLoadFunction.Description: Optional function to load a tile given a URL.

TilePixelRatio.Name: Tile Pixel Ratio
TilePixelRatio.Description: The pixel ratio used by the tile service. For example, if the tile service advertizes 256px by 256px tiles but actually sends 512px by 512px images (for retina/hidpi devices) then tilePixelRatio should be set to 2.

Url.Name: Url
Url.Description: URL template. Must include {x}, {y} or {-y}, and {z} placeholders. A {?-?} template pattern, for example subdomain{a-f}.domain.com, may be used instead of defining each one separately in the urls option

WrapX.Name: WrapX
WrapX.Description: Whether to wrap the world horizontally. The default, undefined, is to request out-of-bounds tiles from the server. When set to false, only one world will be rendered. When set to true, tiles will be requested for one world only, but they will be wrapped horizontally to render multiple worlds.

Description.Value: Provides a source of features for vector layers. Vector features provided by this source are suitable for editing.
Description.Name: Description

Format.Name: Format
Format.Description: The feature format used by the XHR feature loader when url is set. Required if url is set, otherwise ignored.

Loader.Name: Loader Function
Loader.Description: The loader function used to load features, from a remote source for example. Note that the source will create and use an XHR feature loader when url is set.

UseSpatialIndex.Name: Use Spatial Index
UseSpatialIndex.Description: By default, an RTree is used as spatial index. When features are removed and added frequently, and the total number of features is low, setting this to false may improve performance.

WrapX.Name: WrapX
WrapX.Description: Wrap the world horizontally. Default is true. For vector editing across the -180° and 180° meridians to work properly, this should be set to false. The resulting geometry coordinates will then exceed the world bounds.

Description.Value: For layer sources that provide pre-rendered, tiled images in grids that are organized by zoom levels for specific resolutions.
Description.Name: Description

Preload.Name: Preload
Preload.Description: Preload. Load low-resolution tiles up to preload levels. By default preload is 0, which means no preloading.

ZIndex.Name: ZIndex
ZIndex.Description: The z-index for layer rendering. At rendering time, the layers will be ordered, first by Z-index and then by position.

Extent.Name: Extent
Extent.Description: The bounding extent for layer rendering. The layer will not be rendered outside of this extent: [MinX, MinY, MaxX, MaxY]

MinResolution.Name: Minimum Resolution
MinResolution.Description: The minimum resolution (inclusive) at which this layer will be visible.

MaxResolution.Name: Maximum Resolution
MaxResolution.Description: The maximum resolution (exclusive) below which this layer will be visible.

Description.Value: Layer for rendering vector data as a heatmap dynamically
Description.Name: Description

Gradient.Name: Gradient
Gradient.Description: The color gradient of the heatmap, specified as an array of CSS color strings.

CurrentTime.Name: Last Animation Frame
CurrentTime.Description: In Epoch Time from Start Time

WaitTime.Name: Wait Time
WaitTime.Description: Duration of each timestep in animation

IsLooping.Name: Loop Animation
IsLooping.Description: When set to true, the layer animation will loop
